3. CONSERVATIVE PROVISIONS

3.1. No Privilege Escalation

     The Software shall not be used to implement, enable, or facilitate
     privilege escalation mechanisms including but not limited to:
     - Root access systems (sudo, su, doas)
     - Setuid/setgid binaries
     - Capability elevation
     - Kernel-level privilege grants

3.2. API-First Architecture

     Implementations should prefer API-based access control over
     traditional Unix permission models where feasible.

3.3. Attribution

     The names "Prism-IQ", "Zoe", and contributor names may not be used
     to endorse derived products without prior written permission.

